Description:
    Wires the app for collaborative documents: a DocumentChannel speaking
    the y-websocket protocol, an update-log model backed by
    Y::ActionCable::UpdateLog (append-only rows with compaction), and its
    migration.

The optional argument names the update-log model; the table and the
migration derive from it, so nothing forces the yrby prefix on your
schema:

Example:
    bin/rails generate yrby:install
    bin/rails generate yrby:install DocumentRevision

    This will create:
        app/channels/document_channel.rb
        app/models/yrby_document_update.rb
        db/migrate/XXXXXXXX_create_yrby_document_updates.rb
